1
00:01:36,960 --> 00:01:40,150
[Born to Be Alive]

2
00:01:40,180 --> 00:01:43,200
[Episode 17]

3
00:01:46,500 --> 00:01:47,700
It's for you to drink.

4
00:01:48,729 --> 00:01:50,039
I'm not Han.

5
00:01:50,070 --> 00:01:51,050
I'm not into it.

6
00:01:53,600 --> 00:01:55,200
I think you need a drink.

7
00:02:03,740 --> 00:02:05,490
You seem more mature now.

8
00:02:06,300 --> 00:02:08,360
You don't even argue with me anymore.

9
00:02:09,900 --> 00:02:10,900
You want to argue?

10
00:02:12,190 --> 00:02:13,790
It's no fun arguing with you.

11
00:02:14,040 --> 00:02:15,240
You never win anyway.

12
00:02:16,960 --> 00:02:18,420
Who could win against you?

13
00:02:24,530 --> 00:02:25,120
Is it because

14
00:02:25,120 --> 00:02:26,340
Shao Yunfei left?

15
00:02:32,290 --> 00:02:32,970
Maybe,

16
00:02:33,880 --> 00:02:34,740
but not really.

17
00:02:37,079 --> 00:02:37,720
His report

18
00:02:37,750 --> 00:02:39,280
got published, but so what?

19
00:02:41,520 --> 00:02:42,680
Besides us,

20
00:02:44,360 --> 00:02:47,200
hardly anyone cares.

21
00:02:48,150 --> 00:02:49,350
Of course it matters.

22
00:02:52,000 --> 00:02:52,800
Liu and Jiumei

23
00:02:52,800 --> 00:02:53,780
came back

24
00:02:53,800 --> 00:02:55,460
because they read his report.

25
00:02:56,810 --> 00:02:57,740
Every footprint

26
00:02:57,740 --> 00:02:58,810
we leave here

27
00:03:00,190 --> 00:03:01,630
is only visible to us.

28
00:03:04,050 --> 00:03:04,730
Bolamula

29
00:03:04,750 --> 00:03:06,070
is an unknown world

30
00:03:07,370 --> 00:03:08,710
to outsiders.

31
00:03:10,900 --> 00:03:12,360
Now that the report is out,

32
00:03:13,810 --> 00:03:15,540
even if one more person sees it,

33
00:03:16,079 --> 00:03:16,890
it means

34
00:03:17,220 --> 00:03:19,150
we've taken another step forward.

35
00:03:21,490 --> 00:03:22,360
Maybe this can be

36
00:03:22,360 --> 00:03:23,760
seen as a starting point.

37
00:03:24,970 --> 00:03:26,400
And that is enough.

38
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:34,320
Shao Yunfei wrote in his report

39
00:03:36,900 --> 00:03:38,829
that what our Mountain Patrol does

40
00:03:40,150 --> 00:03:41,120
is essentially

41
00:03:42,690 --> 00:03:43,370
one tree

42
00:03:44,650 --> 00:03:46,000
shaking another tree,

43
00:03:47,630 --> 00:03:48,430
one cloud

44
00:03:49,190 --> 00:03:50,520
pushing another cloud,

45
00:03:52,079 --> 00:03:53,020
and one soul

46
00:03:54,190 --> 00:03:55,590
awakening another soul.

47
00:03:58,079 --> 00:03:59,880
Yet he himself wasn't awakened.

48
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:02,900
Wasn't he?

49
00:04:04,590 --> 00:04:06,080
If he had been,

50
00:04:07,560 --> 00:04:08,820
he wouldn't have left.

51
00:04:18,860 --> 00:04:19,570
What counts as

52
00:04:19,570 --> 00:04:20,579
truly leaving?

53
00:04:23,510 --> 00:04:24,770
People are different.

54
00:04:26,040 --> 00:04:26,740
Some people think

55
00:04:26,740 --> 00:04:27,950
life is too short

56
00:04:29,610 --> 00:04:31,170
to stay in one place

57
00:04:31,690 --> 00:04:33,020
for too long.

58
00:04:35,310 --> 00:04:36,750
But for us,

59
00:04:38,760 --> 00:04:40,170
burning out our lives

60
00:04:40,700 --> 00:04:41,680
in one place

61
00:04:43,000 --> 00:04:44,400
is living to the fullest.

62
00:04:46,490 --> 00:04:47,490
Neither is wrong.

63
00:04:53,270 --> 00:04:54,300
Bai Shao left.

64
00:04:57,150 --> 00:04:58,350
Shao Yunfei left too.

65
00:05:03,370 --> 00:05:04,250
In your life,

66
00:05:05,690 --> 00:05:07,290
someone always has to leave.

67
00:05:10,710 --> 00:05:12,310
We'll all leave eventually.

68
00:05:27,850 --> 00:05:28,640
Alright, alright.

69
00:05:28,640 --> 00:05:29,370
Give it to me.

70
00:05:37,320 --> 00:05:38,580
Seeing you like this

71
00:05:39,490 --> 00:05:40,380
reminds me of

72
00:05:40,409 --> 00:05:41,570
when I was young.

73
00:05:43,370 --> 00:05:44,560
Back then, the County Hospital

74
00:05:44,560 --> 00:05:46,159
didn't even have a building.

75
00:05:46,740 --> 00:05:48,070
There were just 3 tents.

76
00:05:48,890 --> 00:05:50,120
A female doctor

77
00:05:50,140 --> 00:05:51,940
was assigned here from Nanjing.

78
00:05:53,450 --> 00:05:54,690
She was so beautiful.

79
00:05:56,230 --> 00:05:57,960
Many of our Tibetan young men

80
00:05:58,010 --> 00:05:59,150
chased after her.

81
00:06:01,920 --> 00:06:03,410
I wonder who

82
00:06:03,520 --> 00:06:04,780
she ended up marrying.

83
00:06:05,760 --> 00:06:06,650
Duo!

84
00:06:06,990 --> 00:06:08,220
You must be drunk!

85
00:06:08,950 --> 00:06:10,080
What did you call me?

86
00:06:10,220 --> 00:06:11,750
You're the one who's drunk.

87
00:06:36,870 --> 00:06:37,770
Here's one!

88
00:06:38,430 --> 00:06:39,159
Let me see!

89
00:06:40,840 --> 00:06:41,550
The stem is so short.

90
00:06:41,550 --> 00:06:42,480
It must be thick.

91
00:06:45,090 --> 00:06:46,050
Be careful.

92
00:06:57,810 --> 00:06:58,430
How is it?

93
00:06:59,290 --> 00:07:00,350
The color is great.

94
00:07:00,390 --> 00:07:01,650
How many do we have now?

95
00:07:06,890 --> 00:07:07,630
8.

96
00:07:08,180 --> 00:07:09,050
I don't have as many as you.

97
00:07:09,050 --> 00:07:10,100
I only have 5.

98
00:07:13,130 --> 00:07:14,520
If I could dig for Cordyceps every day,

99
00:07:14,520 --> 00:07:15,480
that would be great.

100
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,210
I wouldn't have to go to school.

101
00:07:18,340 --> 00:07:19,170
You and your dad

102
00:07:19,170 --> 00:07:20,430
still don't talk much?

103
00:07:21,950 --> 00:07:22,430
There's still no news

104
00:07:22,430 --> 00:07:23,630
about your brother?

105
00:07:25,040 --> 00:07:25,930
You would know

106
00:07:25,950 --> 00:07:27,400
if there were any news about my brother.

107
00:07:27,400 --> 00:07:28,280
Why ask me?

108
00:07:28,390 --> 00:07:29,320
It's your fault.

109
00:07:29,870 --> 00:07:31,460
You had to hit a sore spot.

110
00:07:32,420 --> 00:07:33,880
Your Chinese has improved a lot.

111
00:07:33,880 --> 00:07:35,280
You have a way with words.

112
00:07:40,650 --> 00:07:42,850
Stop giving your dad the cold shoulder.

113
00:07:43,420 --> 00:07:44,480
I just don't get it.

114
00:07:44,920 --> 00:07:46,220
Why can't adults listen to

115
00:07:46,220 --> 00:07:47,400
what kids want to say

116
00:07:47,640 --> 00:07:49,020
and hear our thoughts?

117
00:07:50,070 --> 00:07:50,690
They used to be

118
00:07:50,690 --> 00:07:52,159
kids themselves.

119
00:07:52,250 --> 00:07:53,000
You don't listen

120
00:07:53,000 --> 00:07:54,220
to your dad either.

121
00:07:54,310 --> 00:07:55,570
It's not that I don't listen.

122
00:07:55,570 --> 00:07:57,230
He just doesn't say anything.

123
00:07:57,430 --> 00:07:59,900
He always thinks
I don't understand anything.

124
00:07:59,900 --> 00:08:01,160
Anyway, you don't have a dad like that.

125
00:08:01,160 --> 00:08:02,620
You wouldn't understand.

126
00:08:16,080 --> 00:08:17,220
I—I'm sorry.

127
00:08:17,240 --> 00:08:18,700
I didn't mean it like that.

128
00:08:21,560 --> 00:08:22,260
When I was little,

129
00:08:22,260 --> 00:08:23,240
my brother and I

130
00:08:23,370 --> 00:08:25,630
went to the neighboring village market.

131
00:08:25,820 --> 00:08:27,620
There was an opera performance.

132
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:28,800
We got so absorbed in the show

133
00:08:28,800 --> 00:08:29,690
that we lost track of time.

134
00:08:29,690 --> 00:08:30,560
It got dark.

135
00:08:31,590 --> 00:08:33,650
We got a good beating when we got home.

136
00:08:35,940 --> 00:08:37,740
My brother was crying beside me.

137
00:08:38,299 --> 00:08:39,500
That's when I thought

138
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,330
I needed to grow up fast.

139
00:08:42,140 --> 00:08:44,200
Once I grew up, I could go out and work.

140
00:08:44,470 --> 00:08:45,940
I'd run far enough away

141
00:08:46,600 --> 00:08:48,090
so he couldn't hit me

142
00:08:48,580 --> 00:08:49,910
or keep me in line again.

143
00:08:53,080 --> 00:08:54,270
But later I realized

144
00:08:55,510 --> 00:08:56,460
having someone to keep you in line

145
00:08:56,460 --> 00:08:57,790
is actually a blessing.

146
00:09:00,460 --> 00:09:01,390
Only people who care about you

147
00:09:01,390 --> 00:09:02,990
would try to keep you in line.

148
00:09:04,240 --> 00:09:04,890
But by the time

149
00:09:04,890 --> 00:09:05,980
I understood this,

150
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:07,820
I was already grown up.

151
00:09:14,500 --> 00:09:16,100
What's your brother's name?

152
00:09:16,200 --> 00:09:16,860
Zhang Yuan.

153
00:09:19,410 --> 00:09:20,550
Zhang Yuan!

154
00:09:21,150 --> 00:09:23,370
We will definitely find you!

155
00:09:24,790 --> 00:09:25,900
Get up! Let's keep digging!

156
00:09:25,900 --> 00:09:28,030
let's earn money to find your brother!

157
00:09:28,040 --> 00:09:29,180
Let's go past them

158
00:09:29,370 --> 00:09:31,030
and dig at the top of the slope.

159
00:09:48,080 --> 00:09:48,740
We're back!

160
00:09:48,770 --> 00:09:49,770
-We're back!
-Ju!

161
00:09:50,180 --> 00:09:51,270
You're back?

162
00:09:51,740 --> 00:09:52,450
Dad!

163
00:09:56,270 --> 00:09:56,820
Captain.

164
00:09:57,200 --> 00:09:57,980
Thank you.

165
00:09:58,100 --> 00:09:58,580
Ju,

166
00:09:58,850 --> 00:10:00,320
any news about my brother?

167
00:10:02,020 --> 00:10:02,660
No.

168
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:05,730
Han.

169
00:10:06,190 --> 00:10:06,940
Have some water.

170
00:10:06,940 --> 00:10:07,320
Okay.

171
00:10:10,170 --> 00:10:11,000
Next time you go into the mountains,

172
00:10:11,000 --> 00:10:12,330
can you take me with you?

173
00:10:12,840 --> 00:10:13,700
You're too young.

174
00:10:13,700 --> 00:10:14,500
You can't go in.

175
00:10:14,500 --> 00:10:15,600
I've been in there before.

176
00:10:15,600 --> 00:10:16,620
Why won't you let me go?

177
00:10:16,620 --> 00:10:17,410
Yeah.

178
00:10:17,500 --> 00:10:18,480
Last time you went in,

179
00:10:18,480 --> 00:10:19,480
you almost died.

180
00:10:19,540 --> 00:10:20,670
Have you forgotten?

181
00:10:24,840 --> 00:10:25,220
Here.

182
00:10:26,890 --> 00:10:27,120
Ju.

183
00:10:27,140 --> 00:10:28,000
That's enough.

184
00:10:28,620 --> 00:10:29,750
Can I drive?

185
00:10:30,340 --> 00:10:32,030
We just got back. We drove for 6 days.

186
00:10:32,030 --> 00:10:32,600
There's no gas left

187
00:10:32,600 --> 00:10:33,720
for you to practice.

188
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:34,530
We have gas.

189
00:10:37,500 --> 00:10:38,630
Where did you get it?

190
00:10:39,270 --> 00:10:40,380
We dug Cordyceps

191
00:10:40,410 --> 00:10:41,430
and herded sheep for others to earn money

192
00:10:41,430 --> 00:10:42,530
and bought the gas ourselves.

193
00:10:42,530 --> 00:10:42,940
Yeah.

194
00:10:43,250 --> 00:10:44,050
Not bad.

195
00:10:45,250 --> 00:10:46,030
Impressive.

196
00:10:49,180 --> 00:10:49,980
Alright then.

197
00:10:51,490 --> 00:10:52,360
Don't drive too far.

198
00:10:52,360 --> 00:10:52,820
When you're done driving,

199
00:10:52,820 --> 00:10:53,600
wash the car for me.

200
00:10:53,600 --> 00:10:54,530
Don't worry, Ju.

201
00:11:01,340 --> 00:11:01,960
Jiumei.

202
00:11:03,050 --> 00:11:04,110
Go with them later.

203
00:11:04,850 --> 00:11:05,500
Okay.

204
00:11:06,230 --> 00:11:07,410
Why is it always me?

205
00:11:08,700 --> 00:11:09,500
What's wrong?

206
00:11:09,610 --> 00:11:10,700
You're so lazy.

207
00:11:14,670 --> 00:11:15,410
This gas

208
00:11:15,590 --> 00:11:17,040
should last 4 hours.

209
00:11:17,150 --> 00:11:18,410
I think more than that.

210
00:11:18,870 --> 00:11:19,390
800 kilometers

211
00:11:19,390 --> 00:11:20,720
shouldn't be a problem.

212
00:11:25,510 --> 00:11:26,100
Captain.

213
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:27,010
Here are the main events

214
00:11:27,010 --> 00:11:27,670
from this period.

215
00:11:27,670 --> 00:11:28,870
I wrote them all down.

216
00:11:28,940 --> 00:11:29,620
Let me see.

217
00:11:33,030 --> 00:11:33,740
Han.

218
00:11:34,700 --> 00:11:36,100
Your family called to ask

219
00:11:36,290 --> 00:11:37,620
how the blind date went.

220
00:11:37,670 --> 00:11:38,600
I'm thinking...

221
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:39,720
It didn't go well.

222
00:11:40,990 --> 00:11:42,110
Who asked you?

223
00:11:42,910 --> 00:11:44,370
Bai Ju, what are you doing?

224
00:11:44,510 --> 00:11:45,130
My coat is wet.

225
00:11:45,130 --> 00:11:45,940
I'm drying it.

226
00:11:48,940 --> 00:11:49,630
He.

227
00:11:50,030 --> 00:11:50,740
The usual—

228
00:11:50,990 --> 00:11:51,800
Go to the county tomorrow

229
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:53,040
to settle accounts with Wangmu.

230
00:11:53,040 --> 00:11:53,510
Okay.

231
00:11:54,510 --> 00:11:55,910
She called to hurry us up.

232
00:11:56,270 --> 00:11:56,910
Twice.

233
00:11:58,270 --> 00:11:58,870
Okay.

234
00:12:03,460 --> 00:12:04,520
Most importantly,

235
00:12:07,100 --> 00:12:07,880
Shao called

236
00:12:07,910 --> 00:12:08,890
a few days ago.

237
00:12:09,510 --> 00:12:10,820
The leaders
from the Provincial Department of Forestry

238
00:12:10,820 --> 00:12:13,000
read his report
and took it very seriously.

239
00:12:13,000 --> 00:12:13,890
They allocated a special fund

240
00:12:13,890 --> 00:12:15,290
for the Mountain Patrol—

241
00:12:15,860 --> 00:12:16,840
100,000 yuan.

242
00:12:17,160 --> 00:12:18,000
100,000?

243
00:12:18,020 --> 00:12:19,980
It'll be transferred to the county soon.

244
00:12:19,980 --> 00:12:20,410
Really?

245
00:12:20,410 --> 00:12:21,550
We finally have money!

246
00:12:21,550 --> 00:12:22,610
That's wonderful!

247
00:12:25,840 --> 00:12:26,890
100,000?

248
00:12:28,060 --> 00:12:29,390
If only it were 400,000.

249
00:12:29,440 --> 00:12:30,320
Then we could even buy

250
00:12:30,320 --> 00:12:31,510
an imported Jeep.

251
00:12:31,870 --> 00:12:32,910
Keep dreaming.

252
00:12:32,940 --> 00:12:34,300
An imported Jeep?

253
00:12:34,480 --> 00:12:35,200
Even if we could afford it,

254
00:12:35,200 --> 00:12:36,930
where would we get it repaired?

255
00:12:37,130 --> 00:12:38,930
100,000 is already good enough.

256
00:12:38,970 --> 00:12:40,650
After paying everyone's wages,

257
00:12:40,650 --> 00:12:41,860
we could even get

258
00:12:41,960 --> 00:12:43,340
a second-hand Beijing Jeep. True.

259
00:12:43,340 --> 00:12:44,070
That's true.

260
00:12:44,100 --> 00:12:44,910
That's still better than the old cars

261
00:12:44,910 --> 00:12:45,650
in the team

262
00:12:45,750 --> 00:12:47,380
that can never keep up with the poachers.

263
00:12:47,380 --> 00:12:48,090
Exactly.

264
00:12:50,060 --> 00:12:50,590
Captain.

265
00:12:51,190 --> 00:12:52,240
Did Reporter Shao...

266
00:12:52,240 --> 00:12:53,300
say anything else?

267
00:12:56,540 --> 00:12:58,420
No, that's it.

268
00:13:15,660 --> 00:13:16,540
I forgot.

269
00:13:17,620 --> 00:13:18,530
Reporter Shao sent something

270
00:13:18,530 --> 00:13:19,200
to Bai.

271
00:13:19,870 --> 00:13:20,820
Go get it!

272
00:13:22,630 --> 00:13:23,530
How can he forget that?

273
00:13:23,530 --> 00:13:24,670
Silly boy.

274
00:13:27,470 --> 00:13:28,250
Here, Ju.

275
00:13:42,920 --> 00:13:44,830
What Shao wrote to Bai

276
00:13:44,930 --> 00:13:46,740
is even longer than his report.

277
00:13:57,760 --> 00:13:58,250
These are all

278
00:13:58,250 --> 00:13:59,850
Forestry Police documents.

279
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:04,000
Not a single word

280
00:14:04,030 --> 00:14:04,890
to Bai?

281
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:06,740
Let me see.

282
00:14:07,170 --> 00:14:07,820
What are you looking for?

283
00:14:07,820 --> 00:14:09,080
You can't read anyway.

284
00:14:09,130 --> 00:14:09,890
Why are you pushing me?

285
00:14:09,890 --> 00:14:10,500
There must be something.

286
00:14:10,500 --> 00:14:11,430
Look carefully.

287
00:14:11,870 --> 00:14:12,580
Bai Ju.

288
00:14:13,390 --> 00:14:13,960
These documents

289
00:14:13,960 --> 00:14:15,690
must be very important, right?

290
00:14:18,430 --> 00:14:19,120
I basically covered everything

291
00:14:19,120 --> 00:14:20,240
in my report.

292
00:14:20,790 --> 00:14:21,850
If I waited for him,

293
00:14:21,880 --> 00:14:23,010
it would be too late.

294
00:14:24,080 --> 00:14:25,010
If there's nothing else tonight,

295
00:14:25,010 --> 00:14:26,330
I'll go back to the county.

296
00:14:26,330 --> 00:14:27,790
I'll stay at home tonight.

297
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:31,290
Is she upset?

298
00:14:32,530 --> 00:14:35,260
I'm just going back to the bureau
to submit the report!

299
00:14:35,260 --> 00:14:36,390
She has rabbit ears.

300
00:14:52,000 --> 00:14:52,860
You wrote this?

301
00:14:53,110 --> 00:14:53,780
Yes.

302
00:15:04,480 --> 00:15:05,210
Look at this.

303
00:15:17,030 --> 00:15:17,630
What's written here

304
00:15:17,630 --> 00:15:19,270
is about the same as mine.

305
00:15:25,530 --> 00:15:27,050
It's a bit better...

306
00:15:27,640 --> 00:15:28,490
than mine.

307
00:15:29,590 --> 00:15:30,410
I have been in this position

308
00:15:30,410 --> 00:15:31,270
for 3 years.

309
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:33,910
I've been bringing this up for 3 years,

310
00:15:33,910 --> 00:15:35,480
and every year it gets rejected.

311
00:15:35,480 --> 00:15:36,810
They never approved it.

312
00:15:39,850 --> 00:15:40,870
Why is that?

313
00:15:41,840 --> 00:15:43,370
We both know the importance

314
00:15:43,420 --> 00:15:45,150
of the Forestry Police, right?

315
00:15:45,880 --> 00:15:47,210
So why do you think it is?

316
00:15:52,290 --> 00:15:53,290
There's no money.

317
00:15:59,480 --> 00:16:00,970
Mom, I'm back.

318
00:16:03,210 --> 00:16:04,070
Bai Ji?

319
00:16:06,950 --> 00:16:08,590
Mom, I'm back.

320
00:16:10,740 --> 00:16:11,270
Why didn't you lock the door

321
00:16:11,270 --> 00:16:12,390
when you got out?

322
00:16:17,600 --> 00:16:18,240
Chun!

323
00:16:18,820 --> 00:16:20,280
I'm not dreaming, am I?

324
00:16:20,310 --> 00:16:21,980
Why are you back?

325
00:16:22,120 --> 00:16:23,670
You didn't even tell me
you were coming back.

326
00:16:23,670 --> 00:16:25,510
Why the surprise attack?

327
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:28,410
Let me take a look at you.

328
00:16:29,130 --> 00:16:30,440
When did you get home?

329
00:16:31,190 --> 00:16:32,650
I came in right before you.

330
00:16:32,930 --> 00:16:33,980
You guys.

331
00:16:34,500 --> 00:16:35,220
You didn't lock the yard door,

332
00:16:35,220 --> 00:16:36,950
and you didn't clean the rooms.

333
00:16:37,200 --> 00:16:38,050
Yeah, yeah, yeah.

334
00:16:38,050 --> 00:16:39,150
You're the model soldier.

335
00:16:39,150 --> 00:16:40,840
The first thing you did
when you got back was housework.

336
00:16:40,840 --> 00:16:41,980
Should I give you
a big red flower as a reward?

337
00:16:41,980 --> 00:16:42,710
Give it to me.

338
00:16:44,680 --> 00:16:45,310
Chun,

339
00:16:46,030 --> 00:16:47,670
what merit did you earn this time?

340
00:16:47,670 --> 00:16:48,730
What medal is this?

341
00:16:53,700 --> 00:16:55,300
It's a commemorative medal.

342
00:16:57,540 --> 00:16:58,800
Commemorative medal?

343
00:17:02,240 --> 00:17:02,790
Chun,

344
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:06,010
where are your epaulets and collar tabs?

345
00:17:09,359 --> 00:17:10,690
I'm out of the military.

346
00:17:18,359 --> 00:17:19,220
Is it good, Mom?

347
00:17:19,250 --> 00:17:19,700
It's delicious.

348
00:17:19,700 --> 00:17:20,640
It's good.

349
00:17:22,099 --> 00:17:24,500
You should have told us
you were coming back

350
00:17:24,609 --> 00:17:26,470
so I could make dumplings for you.

351
00:17:26,829 --> 00:17:27,980
Your first meal back home

352
00:17:27,980 --> 00:17:29,610
ended up with you cooking.

353
00:17:30,920 --> 00:17:31,970
And you.

354
00:17:32,480 --> 00:17:34,230
You came back even later than me.

355
00:17:34,230 --> 00:17:35,490
Mom, we got off work...

356
00:17:35,880 --> 00:17:37,790
There will be plenty of chances
in the future.

357
00:17:37,790 --> 00:17:38,990
Dumplings are for leaving,
and noodles are for coming home.

358
00:17:38,990 --> 00:17:39,700
Bai Ju was just craving

359
00:17:39,700 --> 00:17:41,430
the minced meat noodles I make.

360
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:43,290
They are tasty,

361
00:17:43,400 --> 00:17:44,700
but you're too biased, Chun.

362
00:17:44,700 --> 00:17:45,240
These two dishes

363
00:17:45,240 --> 00:17:46,090
are both Ju's favorites.

364
00:17:46,090 --> 00:17:46,850
You didn't make
the "Three Braised Delicacies"

365
00:17:46,850 --> 00:17:47,460
I like.

366
00:17:47,660 --> 00:17:49,250
I'll make it for you tomorrow.

367
00:17:49,250 --> 00:17:49,720
Okay.

368
00:17:49,970 --> 00:17:51,430
Tomorrow Bai Ji will cook.

369
00:17:51,860 --> 00:17:53,400
Show your cooking skills to your brother.

370
00:17:53,400 --> 00:17:53,730
Okay.

371
00:17:53,850 --> 00:17:54,670
My sister said

372
00:17:54,700 --> 00:17:55,290
my cooking

373
00:17:55,290 --> 00:17:56,500
has improved a lot,

374
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:58,250
almost catching up with yours.

375
00:17:58,250 --> 00:17:59,070
That's enough.

376
00:17:59,070 --> 00:18:00,550
I was just encouraging you.

377
00:18:00,550 --> 00:18:01,290
Compared to our brother,

378
00:18:01,290 --> 00:18:02,690
you're still far behind.

379
00:18:03,550 --> 00:18:04,050
Right.

380
00:18:05,290 --> 00:18:05,780
Chun.

381
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,810
Why are you suddenly out of the military?

382
00:18:07,810 --> 00:18:08,900
Didn't you say in your letter before

383
00:18:08,900 --> 00:18:10,900
that you were going to get promoted?

384
00:18:11,550 --> 00:18:12,220
Our cavalry battalion

385
00:18:12,220 --> 00:18:12,940
has been downsized

386
00:18:12,940 --> 00:18:13,810
into a company.

387
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:15,290
Veterans like us

388
00:18:15,770 --> 00:18:17,300
have all been demobilized.

389
00:18:17,420 --> 00:18:18,030
You're the last person

390
00:18:18,030 --> 00:18:19,670
who should have been demobilized.

391
00:18:19,670 --> 00:18:20,900
You've earned merits.

392
00:18:20,900 --> 00:18:22,010
Reducing its permanent positions

393
00:18:22,010 --> 00:18:22,640
is part of

394
00:18:22,660 --> 00:18:23,850
the military's modernization reform.

395
00:18:23,850 --> 00:18:25,000
It's not about individuals.

396
00:18:25,000 --> 00:18:27,400
I had to follow the organization's orders.

397
00:18:27,400 --> 00:18:29,330
You really see the bigger picture.

398
00:18:30,150 --> 00:18:31,280
So what's next?

399
00:18:31,880 --> 00:18:33,810
Have you been assigned a work unit?

400
00:18:33,840 --> 00:18:34,640
I have to wait for the notice.

401
00:18:34,640 --> 00:18:35,800
It won't be that fast.

402
00:18:35,800 --> 00:18:37,330
Should we go find Uncle Lin?

403
00:18:44,940 --> 00:18:46,540
Let's keep things separate.

404
00:18:46,680 --> 00:18:47,350
Just because

405
00:18:47,350 --> 00:18:47,950
I brought your brother

406
00:18:47,950 --> 00:18:48,890
back from

407
00:18:48,920 --> 00:18:50,320
the Tanggula Mountains,

408
00:18:50,590 --> 00:18:51,460
Uncle Lin and Aunt Zhu

409
00:18:51,460 --> 00:18:52,590
criticized me a lot,

410
00:18:52,640 --> 00:18:53,840
saying I was foolish.

411
00:18:54,900 --> 00:18:55,720
I think...

412
00:18:55,780 --> 00:18:56,970
you could listen to his advice

413
00:18:56,970 --> 00:18:58,410
about work.

414
00:19:00,140 --> 00:19:01,440
It's okay, Mom.

415
00:19:01,530 --> 00:19:01,980
It's not like

416
00:19:01,980 --> 00:19:03,660
the local office won't assign me a job.

417
00:19:03,660 --> 00:19:04,270
I haven't been home

418
00:19:04,270 --> 00:19:05,270
for so many years.

419
00:19:05,450 --> 00:19:06,220
Let me rest for a few days.

420
00:19:06,220 --> 00:19:07,680
Can we not talk about this?

421
00:19:08,730 --> 00:19:09,400
Alright.

422
00:19:12,030 --> 00:19:13,790
Once your job is settled,

423
00:19:14,570 --> 00:19:15,570
I'll help you out.

424
00:19:17,720 --> 00:19:18,720
Help me with what?

425
00:19:19,290 --> 00:19:19,850
What kind of girls

426
00:19:19,850 --> 00:19:21,140
do you like?

427
00:19:21,880 --> 00:19:22,500
There are a few

428
00:19:22,500 --> 00:19:23,960
good ones in our hospital.

429
00:19:25,940 --> 00:19:26,680
What's your type?

430
00:19:26,680 --> 00:19:27,770
What's your type?

431
00:19:27,830 --> 00:19:28,810
Mom is asking you.

432
00:19:28,810 --> 00:19:29,810
Why are you asking me?

433
00:19:29,810 --> 00:19:30,380
I'm asking you,

434
00:19:30,380 --> 00:19:31,980
what kind of boys do you like?

435
00:19:38,610 --> 00:19:39,740
I don't like anyone.

436
00:19:41,910 --> 00:19:42,670
Love

437
00:19:44,630 --> 00:19:46,360
often ends in disappointment.

438
00:19:47,210 --> 00:19:48,250
Either you suffer

439
00:19:48,400 --> 00:19:50,330
the boredom of ending up together,

440
00:19:51,390 --> 00:19:52,350
or the pain

441
00:19:53,480 --> 00:19:55,170
of never being together.

442
00:19:59,270 --> 00:20:00,000
Makes sense.

443
00:20:02,070 --> 00:20:03,180
What sense?

444
00:20:03,660 --> 00:20:05,260
She really has a point there.

445
00:20:05,770 --> 00:20:07,170
Where did you learn that?

446
00:20:07,200 --> 00:20:08,840
You are so pessimistic about love.

447
00:20:08,840 --> 00:20:09,730
From a novel.

448
00:20:09,840 --> 00:20:10,940
Which novel?

449
00:20:14,030 --> 00:20:14,620
I forgot.

450
00:20:17,630 --> 00:20:19,700
Alright, stop reading those useless books.

451
00:20:19,700 --> 00:20:20,300
Eat up.

452
00:20:33,320 --> 00:20:35,710
After selling the cordyceps,
are you still buying film?

453
00:20:35,710 --> 00:20:36,860
The camera is gone,

454
00:20:36,940 --> 00:20:38,010
so I won't buy film.

455
00:20:38,160 --> 00:20:39,190
I'm buying

456
00:20:39,220 --> 00:20:40,330
a Ruyi Horse Whip,

457
00:20:40,740 --> 00:20:42,110
just like King Gesar's

458
00:20:42,140 --> 00:20:43,290
Lucky Horse Whip.

459
00:20:43,660 --> 00:20:45,320
Don't you already have a whip?

460
00:20:46,330 --> 00:20:47,440
It's too old.

461
00:20:47,920 --> 00:20:48,500
Jiongxi and I

462
00:20:48,500 --> 00:20:50,250
are participating in the horse race.

463
00:20:50,250 --> 00:20:51,070
Jiongxi can participate

464
00:20:51,070 --> 00:20:52,160
in the race now?

465
00:20:52,450 --> 00:20:54,350
You haven't ridden it for too long.

466
00:20:54,350 --> 00:20:54,940
Jiongxi runs

467
00:20:54,940 --> 00:20:56,470
faster than lightning now.

468
00:20:56,590 --> 00:20:58,390
He even beat Sangje's champion.

469
00:20:59,770 --> 00:21:00,830
Alright, alright.

470
00:21:01,060 --> 00:21:01,760
Whatever.

471
00:21:04,880 --> 00:21:07,680
Did everything go well
in the mountains this time?

472
00:21:10,160 --> 00:21:11,890
The weather is getting warmer,

473
00:21:12,160 --> 00:21:14,420
so fewer people
are hunting Tibetan antelopes.

474
00:21:14,420 --> 00:21:15,140
More people

475
00:21:15,220 --> 00:21:16,110
are panning for placer gold

476
00:21:16,110 --> 00:21:17,710
and catching brine shrimps.

477
00:21:17,960 --> 00:21:19,090
That's a good thing.

478
00:21:19,490 --> 00:21:20,830
With fewer people hunting,

479
00:21:20,830 --> 00:21:22,180
there are fewer guns.

480
00:21:25,160 --> 00:21:25,810
Have you been to

481
00:21:25,810 --> 00:21:26,740
Dolma's place?

482
00:21:28,810 --> 00:21:30,410
We didn't go there this time.

483
00:21:31,290 --> 00:21:32,820
We took the southern route—

484
00:21:34,980 --> 00:21:35,850
Zhuoyuan Lake,

485
00:21:35,980 --> 00:21:37,040
Moon Goddess Lake,

486
00:21:37,350 --> 00:21:38,210
and Pala Slope.

487
00:21:52,230 --> 00:21:53,120
Still awake?

488
00:21:53,830 --> 00:21:54,890
What are you doing?

489
00:21:59,890 --> 00:22:01,020
Don't play too long.

490
00:22:02,110 --> 00:22:03,170
It wastes lamp oil.

491
00:22:07,000 --> 00:22:08,060
I'm going to sleep.

492
00:22:36,900 --> 00:22:37,330
Chun.

493
00:22:37,810 --> 00:22:38,940
Where are you going?

494
00:22:39,450 --> 00:22:40,800
Mom told me yesterday

495
00:22:41,500 --> 00:22:43,000
to make sure

496
00:22:43,050 --> 00:22:44,000
you change

497
00:22:44,030 --> 00:22:44,830
your bedding.

498
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,090
She said if you keep putting it off,

499
00:22:47,090 --> 00:22:48,590
it'll cause lice.

500
00:22:48,940 --> 00:22:50,360
I'm not that dirty.

501
00:22:51,740 --> 00:22:53,270
Where did you get this bike?

502
00:22:53,680 --> 00:22:54,310
From the agricultural station.

503
00:22:54,310 --> 00:22:55,770
I borrowed it from Suonan.

504
00:22:57,090 --> 00:22:58,070
It looks nice.

505
00:23:00,210 --> 00:23:00,770
Let's go.

506
00:23:01,200 --> 00:23:01,770
Get on.

507
00:23:02,740 --> 00:23:03,740
Carry this for me.

508
00:23:04,000 --> 00:23:04,410
Okay.

509
00:23:08,950 --> 00:23:09,450
Chun.

510
00:23:10,910 --> 00:23:12,550
Do you know how to ride a motorcycle?

511
00:23:12,550 --> 00:23:14,220
Iron horses should be about the same

512
00:23:14,220 --> 00:23:15,480
as real horses, right?

513
00:23:17,440 --> 00:23:17,900
Chun!

514
00:23:18,320 --> 00:23:19,600
Slow down!

515
00:23:54,740 --> 00:23:55,370
Not bad.

516
00:23:55,470 --> 00:23:56,270
Not too dirty.

517
00:23:56,730 --> 00:23:57,990
No lice yet.

518
00:23:58,440 --> 00:23:59,140
I told you.

519
00:23:59,190 --> 00:24:01,050
Mom's just worrying for nothing.

520
00:24:03,000 --> 00:24:03,700
Chun,

521
00:24:03,790 --> 00:24:04,430
about the job,

522
00:24:04,430 --> 00:24:05,430
what's your plan?

523
00:24:09,400 --> 00:24:10,770
Why don't you go to our bureau?

524
00:24:10,770 --> 00:24:12,220
We can be police together.

525
00:24:12,220 --> 00:24:13,040
Wasn't Dad

526
00:24:13,070 --> 00:24:14,050
transferred from the army to the police?

527
00:24:14,050 --> 00:24:15,180
Dad was reassigned.

528
00:24:15,260 --> 00:24:16,330
I was demobilized.

529
00:24:16,730 --> 00:24:18,590
The Public Security Bureau is a good unit.

530
00:24:18,590 --> 00:24:19,990
I may not be able to get in.

531
00:24:22,630 --> 00:24:25,090
Isn't your Mountain Patrol
short of people?

532
00:24:25,100 --> 00:24:26,380
How about I stay here?

533
00:24:29,830 --> 00:24:30,940
If you come here,

534
00:24:31,660 --> 00:24:33,060
I'll be happy, of course.

535
00:24:33,280 --> 00:24:34,280
I bet the Captain

536
00:24:34,400 --> 00:24:35,450
will be happy too.

537
00:24:38,450 --> 00:24:39,560
But it's enough

538
00:24:40,250 --> 00:24:41,820
that I jump into this fire pit alone.

539
00:24:41,820 --> 00:24:43,440
Let's not drag the whole family in.

540
00:24:43,440 --> 00:24:44,270
Fire pit?

541
00:24:46,480 --> 00:24:47,440
Didn't you...

542
00:24:48,110 --> 00:24:50,110
say you were satisfied working here?

543
00:24:50,110 --> 00:24:51,870
I am satisfied,

544
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:52,810
but at least I still get a salary

545
00:24:52,810 --> 00:24:53,850
from the bureau.

546
00:24:54,520 --> 00:24:55,670
If you work here,

547
00:24:55,850 --> 00:24:57,340
even feeding yourself will be a problem.

548
00:24:57,340 --> 00:24:58,200
I'm afraid you won't even

549
00:24:58,200 --> 00:24:59,240
be able to find a wife.

550
00:24:59,240 --> 00:25:00,500
You're exaggerating.

551
00:25:03,790 --> 00:25:04,960
Has that reporter from the province

552
00:25:04,960 --> 00:25:05,700
gone back?

553
00:25:07,620 --> 00:25:09,220
Why are you asking about him?

554
00:25:10,160 --> 00:25:10,960
I mean,

555
00:25:11,050 --> 00:25:11,530
the publicity

556
00:25:11,530 --> 00:25:12,460
he did for you guys—

557
00:25:12,460 --> 00:25:13,450
did it help?

558
00:25:15,220 --> 00:25:16,070
Hard to say.

559
00:25:16,400 --> 00:25:17,800
No one is counting on him.

560
00:25:20,660 --> 00:25:21,740
Will he come back?

561
00:25:22,750 --> 00:25:23,480
I don't know.

562
00:25:23,640 --> 00:25:25,170
It has nothing to do with me.

563
00:25:25,680 --> 00:25:26,680
Officer Bai!

564
00:25:27,180 --> 00:25:27,920
Bai Ju!

565
00:25:28,240 --> 00:25:29,140
Come here!

566
00:25:31,930 --> 00:25:33,220
Chun, I'm going down.

567
00:25:38,220 --> 00:25:39,070
What?

568
00:25:43,510 --> 00:25:44,290
What?

569
00:25:45,330 --> 00:25:45,720
Look at you all,

570
00:25:45,720 --> 00:25:47,090
smiling so slyly.

571
00:25:48,910 --> 00:25:50,630
We've decided.

572
00:25:53,040 --> 00:25:54,000
The future deputy captain

573
00:25:54,000 --> 00:25:55,200
will be your brother.

574
00:25:56,360 --> 00:25:57,880
That traitor He Qingyuan—

575
00:25:57,900 --> 00:25:58,480
let him be

576
00:25:58,500 --> 00:26:00,230
County Mayor Lin's secretary.

577
00:26:00,550 --> 00:26:01,750
He always wants to...

578
00:26:01,940 --> 00:26:02,920
Shut up!

579
00:26:03,530 --> 00:26:04,090
Boring.

580
00:26:04,220 --> 00:26:04,660
Alright, alright.

581
00:26:04,660 --> 00:26:05,120
Stop it.

582
00:26:05,130 --> 00:26:05,790
Be serious.

583
00:26:06,200 --> 00:26:06,740
Bai.

584
00:26:07,340 --> 00:26:08,380
He's teasing you.

585
00:26:09,270 --> 00:26:10,220
But we all think

586
00:26:10,240 --> 00:26:12,020
it's great your brother is here.

587
00:26:12,020 --> 00:26:13,240
Look, he can shoot,

588
00:26:13,600 --> 00:26:14,750
ride horses,

589
00:26:14,870 --> 00:26:15,870
and drive.

590
00:26:16,480 --> 00:26:17,740
It would be such a waste

591
00:26:18,010 --> 00:26:19,090
if he didn't join the Mountain Patrol.

592
00:26:19,090 --> 00:26:19,780
-Am I right?
-Yes.

593
00:26:19,780 --> 00:26:20,710
I'm telling you,

594
00:26:21,140 --> 00:26:22,090
no one is allowed to tell the Captain

595
00:26:22,090 --> 00:26:23,420
that my brother is back.

596
00:26:23,500 --> 00:26:24,160
Why?

597
00:26:24,720 --> 00:26:25,570
Wouldn't it be good

598
00:26:25,570 --> 00:26:26,250
to patrol with us?

599
00:26:26,250 --> 00:26:27,440
My brother is a demobilized soldier.

600
00:26:27,440 --> 00:26:29,370
Why would he patrol the mountains?

601
00:26:29,660 --> 00:26:30,350
The government will

602
00:26:30,350 --> 00:26:31,280
assign him a job.

603
00:26:36,910 --> 00:26:37,910
Zhacuo, let's go.

604
00:26:38,250 --> 00:26:39,310
On my way here,

605
00:26:39,400 --> 00:26:41,030
I smelled Tudan frying dough cakes.

606
00:26:41,030 --> 00:26:42,760
Come with me to get some. Hurry.

607
00:26:43,350 --> 00:26:44,640
Why don't you go yourself?

608
00:26:44,640 --> 00:26:45,460
Take more!

609
00:26:45,730 --> 00:26:46,500
I always go to ask for food.

610
00:26:46,500 --> 00:26:47,560
He's not giving me any.

611
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:48,620
You have more sway.

612
00:26:48,850 --> 00:26:49,910
Let's go, let's go.

613
00:27:20,710 --> 00:27:24,750
[Shao Yunfei]

614
00:27:43,440 --> 00:27:44,310
Model soldier.

615
00:27:45,220 --> 00:27:46,330
Working again?

616
00:27:48,520 --> 00:27:50,180
How's the lunch box business?

617
00:27:50,350 --> 00:27:51,280
The business...

618
00:27:51,640 --> 00:27:52,750
is okay.

619
00:27:54,140 --> 00:27:55,590
I just can't raise the price.

620
00:27:55,590 --> 00:27:56,720
Just breaking even.

621
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:58,720
Small businesses thrive on

622
00:27:58,720 --> 00:27:59,610
low margins and high turnover.

623
00:27:59,610 --> 00:28:00,470
That's not bad.

624
00:28:01,710 --> 00:28:02,970
Isn't Yan helping you?

625
00:28:04,480 --> 00:28:05,330
Chun.

626
00:28:07,010 --> 00:28:07,790
Why did Second Sister

627
00:28:07,790 --> 00:28:08,990
tell you everything?

628
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:11,080
She mentioned it in a letter.

629
00:28:11,450 --> 00:28:12,690
So tell me about it.

630
00:28:14,590 --> 00:28:16,190
There's nothing much to say.

631
00:28:17,240 --> 00:28:18,240
She's a doctor.

632
00:28:18,660 --> 00:28:20,200
The boys around her

633
00:28:20,440 --> 00:28:21,970
either came from big cities

634
00:28:22,020 --> 00:28:23,480
or went to medical school.

635
00:28:24,550 --> 00:28:25,530
What am I?

636
00:28:26,750 --> 00:28:27,700
To put it nicely,

637
00:28:28,100 --> 00:28:29,630
I'm a small business owner.

638
00:28:30,640 --> 00:28:31,710
To put it bluntly,

639
00:28:33,760 --> 00:28:35,620
I'm just an unemployed young man.

640
00:28:37,070 --> 00:28:38,070
Yan said that?

641
00:28:38,120 --> 00:28:39,160
Of course not.

642
00:28:39,310 --> 00:28:41,040
She wouldn't say that about me.

643
00:28:43,480 --> 00:28:45,200
All work is equally honorable.

644
00:28:45,200 --> 00:28:46,460
Every trade has its...

645
00:28:46,460 --> 00:28:47,250
Chun, Chun.

646
00:28:47,640 --> 00:28:48,620
Go down and eat.

647
00:28:49,270 --> 00:28:50,000
I'll do this.

648
00:28:50,190 --> 00:28:50,720
I've got several

649
00:28:50,720 --> 00:28:51,720
lunch boxes left.

650
00:28:52,940 --> 00:28:53,800
I'm not hungry.

651
00:28:55,340 --> 00:28:56,740
Let's just talk for a bit.

652
00:28:57,350 --> 00:28:58,280
Talk about what?

653
00:28:58,640 --> 00:28:59,790
Give me a pep talk?

654
00:29:00,640 --> 00:29:02,170
It's always the same stuff,

655
00:29:02,510 --> 00:29:04,380
telling me to keep my feet on the ground,

656
00:29:04,380 --> 00:29:05,220
work hard,

657
00:29:05,570 --> 00:29:06,700
and show some drive.

658
00:29:06,920 --> 00:29:07,350
I'd already

659
00:29:07,350 --> 00:29:08,480
heard all that before I even went

660
00:29:08,480 --> 00:29:09,260
to Tanggula.

661
00:29:09,880 --> 00:29:11,010
I hadn't even gotten

662
00:29:11,140 --> 00:29:11,750
to Lin Daiyu's first appearance

663
00:29:11,750 --> 00:29:12,520
in Dream of the Red Chamber

664
00:29:12,520 --> 00:29:13,920
before I was called back.

665
00:29:15,970 --> 00:29:16,460
Chun.

666
00:29:17,330 --> 00:29:18,850
Times have changed.

667
00:29:19,270 --> 00:29:20,730
Drive alone isn't enough.

668
00:29:23,460 --> 00:29:24,240
You need to know

669
00:29:24,240 --> 00:29:25,550
your own limits.

670
00:29:25,960 --> 00:29:27,070
Haven't you learned enough
from the setbacks

671
00:29:27,070 --> 00:29:27,880
you've had?

672
00:29:28,420 --> 00:29:29,440
Even if you could pick

673
00:29:29,440 --> 00:29:30,480
any job now,

674
00:29:30,710 --> 00:29:32,110
what can you actually do?

675
00:29:36,080 --> 00:29:37,610
I want to open a restaurant.

676
00:29:39,380 --> 00:29:40,070
Even if

677
00:29:40,180 --> 00:29:41,310
it just has 2 tables,

678
00:29:41,790 --> 00:29:43,380
at least it'd be my own place.

679
00:29:43,380 --> 00:29:44,290
I'd be the boss.

680
00:29:46,010 --> 00:29:47,240
That way I'd have something to strive for.

681
00:29:47,240 --> 00:29:47,920
When I make money,

682
00:29:47,920 --> 00:29:49,050
I'll take care of Mom

683
00:29:49,160 --> 00:29:50,620
and build her a nice house.

684
00:29:51,290 --> 00:29:52,620
Lin Jianshe never needs

685
00:29:52,710 --> 00:29:54,310
to worry about finding a job.

686
00:29:54,900 --> 00:29:55,600
If I'd grown up

687
00:29:55,600 --> 00:29:56,470
in his family,

688
00:29:57,670 --> 00:29:59,270
I'd be doing better than him.

689
00:30:02,740 --> 00:30:05,800
I joined the army
and hadn't been relying on the family,

690
00:30:05,950 --> 00:30:07,880
so my portion went to you and Bai Ju.

691
00:30:08,140 --> 00:30:10,070
You got to go to high school, right?

692
00:30:10,190 --> 00:30:11,520
You chose to quit school

693
00:30:11,840 --> 00:30:14,090
and didn't take the college entrance exam.

694
00:30:14,090 --> 00:30:14,930
Lin Jianshe,

695
00:30:14,950 --> 00:30:15,830
no matter how bad he was,

696
00:30:15,830 --> 00:30:16,630
got into a university

697
00:30:16,630 --> 00:30:17,850
in the provincial capital on his own.

698
00:30:17,850 --> 00:30:19,450
Why compare yourself to him?

699
00:30:20,000 --> 00:30:21,000
What's the point?

700
00:30:35,160 --> 00:30:35,750
Ever since I was a kid,

701
00:30:35,750 --> 00:30:36,790
good things

702
00:30:37,770 --> 00:30:38,510
either never

703
00:30:39,960 --> 00:30:41,240
came my way,

704
00:30:42,160 --> 00:30:42,860
or gone

705
00:30:44,920 --> 00:30:45,980
as soon as they did.

706
00:30:48,910 --> 00:30:50,890
Why am I always so unlucky?

707
00:30:54,440 --> 00:30:57,170
Actually,
I was about to get promoted to officer,

708
00:30:59,210 --> 00:31:01,140
but then the downsizing happened.

709
00:31:03,240 --> 00:31:04,700
I didn't expect it either.

710
00:31:06,340 --> 00:31:06,970
But

711
00:31:06,990 --> 00:31:08,050
so what?

712
00:31:15,470 --> 00:31:16,640
When trouble comes,

713
00:31:16,990 --> 00:31:18,520
we just have to deal with it.

714
00:31:20,360 --> 00:31:21,860
I keep reminding myself

715
00:31:23,500 --> 00:31:24,550
not to think I'm the most miserable

716
00:31:24,550 --> 00:31:25,680
or unlucky person

717
00:31:25,700 --> 00:31:26,450
in the world.

718
00:31:29,740 --> 00:31:30,670
Look at Mom.

719
00:31:31,850 --> 00:31:33,110
Before she was even 20,

720
00:31:33,460 --> 00:31:34,090
she left Nanjing,

721
00:31:34,090 --> 00:31:34,740
her home,

722
00:31:34,760 --> 00:31:36,290
and came to this poor place,

723
00:31:36,770 --> 00:31:38,070
working and living in 3 tents

724
00:31:38,070 --> 00:31:39,130
for 2 years.

725
00:31:40,120 --> 00:31:41,980
Have you ever heard her complain?

726
00:31:43,810 --> 00:31:45,180
When life gets hard,

727
00:31:45,610 --> 00:31:46,700
think about how people of their generation

728
00:31:46,700 --> 00:31:47,830
made it through.

729
00:31:48,090 --> 00:31:49,590
Maybe that hurdle in your heart

730
00:31:49,590 --> 00:31:51,590
won't seem so hard to cross anymore.

731
00:31:56,840 --> 00:31:58,240
What are you waiting for?

732
00:31:59,070 --> 00:31:59,850
Get to work.

733
00:32:14,460 --> 00:32:15,770
The sudden cutoff of the Manri River

734
00:32:15,770 --> 00:32:16,290
has caused

735
00:32:16,290 --> 00:32:17,980
huge trouble for our township.

736
00:32:17,980 --> 00:32:19,180
Our livestock numbers

737
00:32:19,180 --> 00:32:20,270
had just started to rise.

738
00:32:20,270 --> 00:32:21,030
And now?

739
00:32:21,350 --> 00:32:22,740
There's no water for them.

740
00:32:22,740 --> 00:32:24,470
Some have already fallen sick.

741
00:32:25,000 --> 00:32:25,960
Even drinking water for the herdsmen

742
00:32:25,960 --> 00:32:27,290
is in very short supply.

743
00:32:27,290 --> 00:32:28,750
They have to search for water everywhere,

744
00:32:28,750 --> 00:32:30,350
and conflicts have started.

745
00:32:30,420 --> 00:32:31,660
Some people even got physical.

746
00:32:31,660 --> 00:32:33,350
It was the people from your township
who started the fight.

747
00:32:33,350 --> 00:32:34,550
We didn't start it.

748
00:32:34,660 --> 00:32:36,120
We're downstream anyway.

749
00:32:36,240 --> 00:32:36,880
You guys ran out of water

750
00:32:36,880 --> 00:32:38,140
and came here looking for it.

751
00:32:38,140 --> 00:32:39,510
What were we supposed to do?

752
00:32:39,510 --> 00:32:40,830
You should go look upstream.

753
00:32:40,830 --> 00:32:41,900
There's no water upstream anymore!

754
00:32:41,900 --> 00:32:43,140
Didn't you hear that just now?

755
00:32:43,140 --> 00:32:43,900
Are you telling me
to go all the way to Geladandong

756
00:32:43,900 --> 00:32:44,420
to find water?

757
00:32:44,420 --> 00:32:45,530
That's not my problem.

758
00:32:45,530 --> 00:32:46,090
If there's another fight,

759
00:32:46,090 --> 00:32:46,950
I can't handle it.

760
00:32:46,950 --> 00:32:47,550
I really can't.

761
00:32:47,550 --> 00:32:48,330
Alright, alright.

762
00:32:48,330 --> 00:32:49,160
Stop arguing.

763
00:32:49,250 --> 00:32:49,850
I didn't call you here

764
00:32:49,850 --> 00:32:50,940
to argue,

765
00:32:51,030 --> 00:32:51,810
but to figure out

766
00:32:51,810 --> 00:32:53,500
why this river dried up.

767
00:32:56,330 --> 00:32:58,330
Normally, with the weather warming up,

768
00:32:58,330 --> 00:32:59,090
snowmelt from the mountains

769
00:32:59,090 --> 00:33:00,530
should be increasing.

770
00:33:01,200 --> 00:33:01,660
So why has this river

771
00:33:01,660 --> 00:33:02,880
run dry?

772
00:33:02,980 --> 00:33:04,110
The cause of the drying up

773
00:33:04,110 --> 00:33:05,370
hasn't been found yet.

774
00:33:05,500 --> 00:33:06,050
There's been a lot of talk

775
00:33:06,050 --> 00:33:07,180
among the herdsmen.

776
00:33:07,290 --> 00:33:08,050
Some of

777
00:33:08,230 --> 00:33:09,510
the older ones say

778
00:33:09,800 --> 00:33:11,460
this is a warning from heaven,

779
00:33:13,030 --> 00:33:14,140
a punishment

780
00:33:14,490 --> 00:33:15,520
for something we did wrong.

781
00:33:15,520 --> 00:33:16,050
Alright.

782
00:33:16,380 --> 00:33:16,970
I got it.

783
00:33:17,970 --> 00:33:19,830
Regarding the herdsmen's beliefs

784
00:33:19,830 --> 00:33:21,010
and customs,

785
00:33:21,890 --> 00:33:22,890
we respect them.

786
00:33:23,720 --> 00:33:24,980
But what I want to know now

787
00:33:24,980 --> 00:33:26,360
is whether you went upstream

788
00:33:26,360 --> 00:33:26,970
to investigate

789
00:33:26,970 --> 00:33:28,810
and if you found the point
where the river ran dry.

790
00:33:28,810 --> 00:33:29,570
We did.

791
00:33:29,680 --> 00:33:30,110
The cutoff point

792
00:33:30,110 --> 00:33:31,810
is not far from Bolamula's boundary.

793
00:33:31,810 --> 00:33:33,240
Searching further inside

794
00:33:33,240 --> 00:33:34,260
would be difficult.

795
00:33:34,260 --> 00:33:35,790
So you just stopped looking?

796
00:33:35,790 --> 00:33:36,590
Keep looking!

797
00:33:36,640 --> 00:33:37,640
County Mayor Lin,

798
00:33:37,800 --> 00:33:39,350
everyone's busy trying to find water.

799
00:33:39,350 --> 00:33:40,480
There's no one left.

800
00:33:45,810 --> 00:33:46,810
County Mayor Lin,

801
00:33:46,900 --> 00:33:48,100
our two townships

802
00:33:48,210 --> 00:33:50,270
want to work together to drill a well,

803
00:33:50,380 --> 00:33:51,150
but we now

804
00:33:51,180 --> 00:33:52,030
have no money.

805
00:33:53,000 --> 00:33:54,270
We operate on a subsistence budget.

806
00:33:54,270 --> 00:33:55,600
Just getting by is hard enough.

807
00:33:55,600 --> 00:33:57,200
We really can't afford this.

808
00:33:58,360 --> 00:34:00,490
County Mayor Lin, our local official,

809
00:34:01,000 --> 00:34:03,200
could you ask the county finance office

810
00:34:03,400 --> 00:34:04,730
to give us some support?

811
00:34:12,389 --> 00:34:13,520
Do you have a...

812
00:34:14,760 --> 00:34:15,650
budget?

813
00:34:16,280 --> 00:34:17,739
About how much do you need?

814
00:34:17,760 --> 00:34:19,280
I asked the drilling team.

815
00:34:19,370 --> 00:34:20,699
At least 100,000 yuan.

816
00:34:41,150 --> 00:34:41,760
Ask them

817
00:34:43,070 --> 00:34:44,070
if 90,000 will do.

818
00:34:44,980 --> 00:34:45,770
I saw it.

819
00:34:45,800 --> 00:34:46,570
The application report

820
00:34:46,570 --> 00:34:47,780
is right on my desk.

821
00:34:48,199 --> 00:34:48,989
Yes, yes.

822
00:34:49,540 --> 00:34:51,400
You don't need to explain it so...

823
00:34:53,000 --> 00:34:54,400
Why is there only 10,000?

824
00:35:00,670 --> 00:35:01,460
I'm asking you why

825
00:35:01,460 --> 00:35:02,460
there is only 10,000.

826
00:35:02,460 --> 00:35:04,060
Because that's all there is.

827
00:35:06,550 --> 00:35:07,750
Reporter Shao told me

828
00:35:08,340 --> 00:35:09,670
there was 100,000 yuan.

829
00:35:12,950 --> 00:35:14,060
That reporter has a loose tongue.

830
00:35:14,060 --> 00:35:15,440
I asked Li from the finance office.

831
00:35:15,440 --> 00:35:16,900
He said the same, 100,000.

832
00:35:17,090 --> 00:35:18,590
So I came here
to ask you, County Mayor Lin.

833
00:35:18,590 --> 00:35:19,030
Why did you

834
00:35:19,030 --> 00:35:20,320
only give us 10,000?

835
00:35:26,030 --> 00:35:26,610
Here.

836
00:35:27,360 --> 00:35:28,110
Sit.

837
00:35:28,380 --> 00:35:29,640
Let's talk about this.

838
00:35:29,830 --> 00:35:30,160
Here.

839
00:35:30,180 --> 00:35:31,580
Explain it clearly to me.

840
00:35:32,590 --> 00:35:33,380
Sit down first.

841
00:35:33,380 --> 00:35:34,800
I'll explain it to you.

842
00:35:43,530 --> 00:35:44,320
The Manri River,

843
00:35:44,320 --> 00:35:46,700
which flows through Quduo Township
and Gela Township,

844
00:35:46,700 --> 00:35:48,430
has suddenly run dry recently.

845
00:35:50,480 --> 00:35:51,170
The water volume of this river

846
00:35:51,170 --> 00:35:52,380
has always been stable.

847
00:35:52,380 --> 00:35:53,840
How did it suddenly dry up?

848
00:35:53,840 --> 00:35:54,920
We don't know yet.

849
00:35:55,270 --> 00:35:56,460
Both people and livestock

850
00:35:56,460 --> 00:35:58,190
have been seriously affected,

851
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:00,670
and there have been some conflicts.

852
00:36:00,670 --> 00:36:02,110
Several people were injured.

853
00:36:02,110 --> 00:36:03,310
So the county decided

854
00:36:03,340 --> 00:36:05,340
to drill a well for the two townships

855
00:36:05,400 --> 00:36:06,840
to minimize the herdsmen's losses

856
00:36:06,840 --> 00:36:07,970
as much as possible.

857
00:36:09,430 --> 00:36:11,050
But you know the county's

858
00:36:11,070 --> 00:36:12,330
financial situation.

859
00:36:12,670 --> 00:36:13,590
We couldn't come up with the money

860
00:36:13,590 --> 00:36:15,320
for drilling a well right away,

861
00:36:17,510 --> 00:36:18,770
so we reallocated the funds meant for

862
00:36:18,770 --> 00:36:20,370
the Mountain Patrol to them.

863
00:36:20,860 --> 00:36:21,480
For those two townships,

864
00:36:21,480 --> 00:36:22,800
that money

865
00:36:22,820 --> 00:36:24,570
is a lifesaver.

866
00:36:24,760 --> 00:36:26,230
Wangjia and Pengcuo said

867
00:36:26,800 --> 00:36:28,170
they would definitely thank you properly.

868
00:36:28,170 --> 00:36:28,780
Those two townships

869
00:36:28,780 --> 00:36:30,090
owe you a big favor.

870
00:36:30,610 --> 00:36:31,410
They even said

871
00:36:31,500 --> 00:36:32,500
they were going to
give your Mountain Patrol

872
00:36:32,500 --> 00:36:33,070
cattle and sheep.

873
00:36:33,070 --> 00:36:34,960
I don't want their cattle or sheep.

874
00:36:34,960 --> 00:36:36,360
This isn't about favors.

875
00:36:36,670 --> 00:36:37,300
Funds must be used for
their specific purpose.

876
00:36:37,300 --> 00:36:38,010
Don't you know that?

877
00:36:38,010 --> 00:36:39,280
I know, I know.

878
00:36:39,690 --> 00:36:41,450
But isn't this a special situation?

879
00:36:41,450 --> 00:36:42,580
Even if I could wait,

880
00:36:42,780 --> 00:36:44,110
the herdsmen couldn't.

881
00:36:44,300 --> 00:36:46,830
Their cattle and sheep
couldn't wait either.

882
00:36:47,810 --> 00:36:48,390
It's true

883
00:36:48,800 --> 00:36:49,440
I didn't

884
00:36:49,550 --> 00:36:50,630
give you a heads-up in advance.

885
00:36:50,630 --> 00:36:51,830
Lin, I'm telling you,

886
00:36:52,510 --> 00:36:53,400
even if you had given me

887
00:36:53,400 --> 00:36:54,660
a heads-up about this,

888
00:36:54,820 --> 00:36:56,150
I wouldn't have agreed.

889
00:36:59,580 --> 00:37:01,380
If you really can't accept it...

890
00:37:01,540 --> 00:37:01,980
Here.

891
00:37:03,380 --> 00:37:04,440
Like I said before—

892
00:37:06,010 --> 00:37:06,860
write a letter

893
00:37:07,020 --> 00:37:07,870
and report me.

894
00:37:09,000 --> 00:37:10,500
Bring Li from finance along.

895
00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:11,760
He can be your witness.

896
00:37:12,110 --> 00:37:12,450
Lin,

897
00:37:12,480 --> 00:37:14,000
are you playing dirty with me again?

898
00:37:14,000 --> 00:37:15,200
Who's playing dirty?

899
00:37:15,420 --> 00:37:16,280
Who's playing dirty?

900
00:37:16,280 --> 00:37:18,340
Who on earth is the one playing dirty?

901
00:37:19,130 --> 00:37:20,000
Why was

902
00:37:20,030 --> 00:37:20,730
Mazhi County

903
00:37:20,730 --> 00:37:22,010
Economic Development Company

904
00:37:22,010 --> 00:37:22,570
established in the first place?

905
00:37:22,570 --> 00:37:23,950
To develop the economy!

906
00:37:24,300 --> 00:37:25,070
And now?

907
00:37:25,440 --> 00:37:26,230
Dalong County, our neighbor,

908
00:37:26,230 --> 00:37:28,150
has made a lot of money from mining.

909
00:37:28,150 --> 00:37:28,900
Their county middle school

910
00:37:28,900 --> 00:37:30,230
has built a new teaching building!

911
00:37:30,230 --> 00:37:31,030
What about us?

912
00:37:31,550 --> 00:37:32,310
Our herdsmen

913
00:37:32,330 --> 00:37:34,390
can't even get clean drinking water.

914
00:37:34,710 --> 00:37:35,900
On one side are the herdsmen's
cattle and sheep.

915
00:37:35,900 --> 00:37:36,420
On the other

916
00:37:36,420 --> 00:37:37,590
are the Tibetan antelopes of Bolamula!

917
00:37:37,590 --> 00:37:38,050
Tell me,

918
00:37:38,150 --> 00:37:39,680
who should this money go to?

919
00:37:41,590 --> 00:37:42,090
Here.

920
00:37:44,280 --> 00:37:45,650
Take this chair.

921
00:37:45,760 --> 00:37:46,340
You tell me

922
00:37:46,340 --> 00:37:47,880
how to handle this.

923
00:37:47,930 --> 00:37:48,810
And I'll go patrol the mountains.

924
00:37:48,810 --> 00:37:49,870
Let's swap places!

925
00:38:26,840 --> 00:38:28,570
Pay back 2,000 to Wangmu first.

926
00:38:29,530 --> 00:38:30,390
Otherwise, next time,

927
00:38:30,390 --> 00:38:31,250
she won't sell anything

928
00:38:31,250 --> 00:38:31,950
to us.

929
00:38:38,840 --> 00:38:39,970
2,000 isn't enough.

930
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:41,580
Then give her 3,000

931
00:38:45,590 --> 00:38:46,200
Then pay everyone

932
00:38:46,200 --> 00:38:47,390
3 months' salary.

933
00:38:51,550 --> 00:38:52,590
The rest

934
00:38:53,210 --> 00:38:53,990
won't even cover

935
00:38:53,990 --> 00:38:55,520
the gas for the next patrol.

936
00:38:58,810 --> 00:39:00,540
Cut the salary by 2 months.

937
00:39:02,280 --> 00:39:03,050
Yeah.

938
00:39:03,420 --> 00:39:04,840
That's fine.

939
00:39:05,940 --> 00:39:07,880
It won't make much difference
at this point.

940
00:39:07,880 --> 00:39:08,650
We haven't been paid

941
00:39:08,650 --> 00:39:09,510
for a long time.

942
00:39:10,010 --> 00:39:11,210
Another two months won't matter.

943
00:39:11,210 --> 00:39:11,820
No.

944
00:39:13,250 --> 00:39:13,750
Pay it.

945
00:40:03,320 --> 00:40:05,540
Should we ask the public for donations?

946
00:40:09,440 --> 00:40:10,720
That would be begging.

947
00:40:14,010 --> 00:40:14,980
What if we issue

948
00:40:15,010 --> 00:40:16,450
a limited number of gold-mining permits

949
00:40:16,450 --> 00:40:17,510
to the fossickers?

950
00:40:19,690 --> 00:40:21,020
Charge for the permits?

951
00:40:22,000 --> 00:40:23,010
Isn't that supporting them

952
00:40:23,010 --> 00:40:24,110
to go mining in there?

953
00:40:24,110 --> 00:40:25,570
It's not supporting them.

954
00:40:25,650 --> 00:40:26,340
You can see it

955
00:40:26,340 --> 00:40:27,500
as a

956
00:40:28,010 --> 00:40:29,210
management measure.

957
00:40:29,670 --> 00:40:30,690
Although we let some people

958
00:40:30,690 --> 00:40:31,610
go in to mine,

959
00:40:31,860 --> 00:40:33,340
it also restricts those

960
00:40:33,420 --> 00:40:34,420
without permits.

961
00:40:36,330 --> 00:40:38,130
Do you think that will stop them?

962
00:40:39,320 --> 00:40:40,250
To put it simply,

963
00:40:40,550 --> 00:40:41,780
they pay for permits,

964
00:40:42,110 --> 00:40:43,190
and we use the money

965
00:40:43,210 --> 00:40:44,690
to support the Mountain Patrol

966
00:40:44,690 --> 00:40:46,340
stopping illegal mining.

967
00:40:47,760 --> 00:40:49,220
What's that called again?

968
00:40:50,480 --> 00:40:52,010
Standardized management.

969
00:40:53,200 --> 00:40:55,730
Looks like you're becoming
County Mayor Lin.

970
00:40:57,430 --> 00:40:58,600
Comrade Duojie,

971
00:40:59,360 --> 00:41:01,750
don't let your personal feelings
get involved.

972
00:41:01,750 --> 00:41:02,250
Yes.

973
00:41:02,760 --> 00:41:03,820
Exactly that tone.

974
00:41:03,930 --> 00:41:04,730
Just like him.

975
00:41:06,570 --> 00:41:07,440
County Mayor Lin

976
00:41:07,440 --> 00:41:09,360
is just doing his job.

977
00:41:10,000 --> 00:41:10,870
You know the situation

978
00:41:10,870 --> 00:41:11,950
in the county.

979
00:41:12,680 --> 00:41:14,430
It's a heavy burden

980
00:41:14,820 --> 00:41:15,950
for anyone to carry.

981
00:41:19,110 --> 00:41:19,860
Yeah.

982
00:41:23,640 --> 00:41:25,840
But placer gold is a national resource.

983
00:41:26,940 --> 00:41:28,070
The Mountain Patrol

984
00:41:29,220 --> 00:41:31,480
doesn't have the right to issue permits.

985
00:41:31,670 --> 00:41:32,650
Then tell me,

986
00:41:32,680 --> 00:41:33,680
what should we do?

987
00:41:39,510 --> 00:41:39,900
First,

988
00:41:39,900 --> 00:41:41,460
I don't agree with issuing permits.

989
00:41:41,460 --> 00:41:42,280
That is shooting ourselves

990
00:41:42,280 --> 00:41:43,300
in the foot.

991
00:41:44,500 --> 00:41:45,980
Once you start issuing permits,

992
00:41:45,980 --> 00:41:46,380
those people

993
00:41:46,380 --> 00:41:48,440
will have more loopholes to exploit.

994
00:41:50,220 --> 00:41:51,680
Let's hold on a bit longer.

995
00:41:54,550 --> 00:41:55,590
Now, Shao's report

996
00:41:55,590 --> 00:41:56,720
has been published.

997
00:41:58,420 --> 00:41:59,440
Since
the Provincial Department of Forestry

998
00:41:59,440 --> 00:42:00,700
allocated funds to us,

999
00:42:01,100 --> 00:42:01,980
it shows that

1000
00:42:02,000 --> 00:42:03,540
they value our work.

1001
00:42:05,140 --> 00:42:06,000
Next,

1002
00:42:06,940 --> 00:42:09,140
Next, when the reserve is established,

1003
00:42:09,150 --> 00:42:10,880
we'll get government funding.

1004
00:42:11,610 --> 00:42:12,380
It will also be easier
to secure permanent positions

1005
00:42:12,380 --> 00:42:13,320
for the team.

1006
00:42:13,900 --> 00:42:14,570
Then

1007
00:42:15,020 --> 00:42:16,350
we can hire more people.

1008
00:42:16,430 --> 00:42:17,430
Wait until when?

1009
00:42:18,340 --> 00:42:20,040
At this rate,
the reserve won't even be established

1010
00:42:20,040 --> 00:42:22,040
before the Mountain Patrol is gone.

1011
00:42:23,650 --> 00:42:26,450
You can't use the future
to guarantee the present.

1012
00:42:26,750 --> 00:42:28,250
Right now, we need money.

1013
00:42:29,280 --> 00:42:30,010
With money,

1014
00:42:30,250 --> 00:42:31,810
we could buy another vehicle

1015
00:42:31,810 --> 00:42:33,210
and recruit more people.

1016
00:42:33,900 --> 00:42:34,920
That's such a huge area,

1017
00:42:34,920 --> 00:42:35,580
and with only 2 cars,

1018
00:42:35,580 --> 00:42:36,910
how can we patrol it all?

1019
00:42:37,340 --> 00:42:39,130
Right now, not to mention recruiting,

1020
00:42:39,130 --> 00:42:40,130
we can't even pay He Qingyuan

1021
00:42:40,130 --> 00:42:40,950
and the others' salaries.

1022
00:42:40,950 --> 00:42:41,840
If in the future the Mountain Patrol

1023
00:42:41,840 --> 00:42:42,460
is left with just the two of us,

1024
00:42:42,460 --> 00:42:44,260
how are we supposed to do the job?

1025
00:42:46,050 --> 00:42:48,110
Even if there's only one person left,

1026
00:42:48,190 --> 00:42:49,390
we have to keep going.

1027
00:42:49,880 --> 00:42:51,090
Stop talking like that.

1028
00:42:51,090 --> 00:42:51,940
So lame.

1029
00:42:52,890 --> 00:42:54,350
You don't allow anything.

1030
00:42:55,460 --> 00:42:56,000
Maybe

1031
00:42:56,320 --> 00:42:57,420
you should just focus on
being Deputy County Mayor

1032
00:42:57,420 --> 00:42:58,550
and climb the ranks.

1033
00:42:58,750 --> 00:43:00,410
When you become County Mayor,

1034
00:43:00,920 --> 00:43:01,880
it'll be your call.
